FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE - TURKEY (THRACE) (03): OIE
********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: 24 Jun 2006
From: ProMED-mail<promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE Disease Information, Vol. 19 - No. 25 9 [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/A_CURRENT.HTM#Sec2>

Foot and Mouth Disease in Turkey in Thrace Region: Follow-Up Report No. 4
Information received on 15 Jun 2006 from Dr H?eyin Sungur, Director
General, General Directorate of Protection and Control, Ministry of
Agriculture and Rural Affairs, Ankara:
End of this report period: 14 Jun 2006.
Identification of agent: foot and mouth disease virus serotype A.
Date of start of the event: 21 Jan 2006.
Details of new outbreak: The outbreak occurred in Evrese village in
Canakkale province, involving 6 cases with 89 susceptible
animals. 19 animals were slaughtered.
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/http://www.oie.int/cartes/19_25_TUR.doc>
Location of the outbreak
Laboratory where diagnostic tests were performed: Foot and Mouth
Institute (national laboratory)
Result: ELISA was positive on 14 Jun 2006
Source of outbreak: introduction of new animals/animal products.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[We are happy to report that considerable progress is obviously being
made by Turkish animal health authorities in this campaign. The last
time we reported on this there were 12 outbreaks involving almost 100
cases with over 10 000 susceptible animals. Good progress indeed. - Mod.PC]
